{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}{{Infobox person | name = Ananta Jalil | image = | native_name = এম এ জলিল অনন্ত | native_name_lang = bn | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Munshiganj District|Munshiganj]], Bangladesh | residence = | nationality = Bangladeshi |alma_mater = | occupation = *[[Actor]] *[[Film director|Director]] *[[Film producer|Producer]] | years_active = 2009–present | spouse = [[Afiea Nusrat Barsha]] | website = {{url|http://anantajalil.info/|http://anantajalil.info}} | image_caption = }} '''Ananta Jalil''' (born '''M.A. Jalil Ananta''') is a [[Bangladeshi]] actor, director, producer, and businessman.<ref>{{cite news |title = Ananta Jalil now turns anchor |url = http://www.dhakatribune.com/entertainment/2014/sep/30/ananta-jalil-now-turns-anchor |newspaper = The Dhaka Tribune |accessdate = 25 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/ananta-jalil-a-phenomenon-or-more|title=ANANTA JALIL A Phenomenon or More?|date=2013-10-03|work=The Daily Star|access-date=2018-02-06|language=en}}</ref> He started professional career as a businessman in 1999, Ananta began his film career with the film ''[[Khoj: The Search]]'' in 2010.<ref name="banglanews24.com">{{cite news |last=Faisal |first=Fahim |date=10 May 2012 |script-title=ডামি নয়, আমিই পাঁচতলা থেকে মাটিতে ঝাঁপ দিলাম : অনন্ত |trans-title= |url=http://www.banglanews24.com/detailsnews.php?nssl=64c06acc9a5858be426c2288782edd68&nttl=10052012110454 |newspaper=banglanews24.com |language=bn |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921201048/http://www.banglanews24.com/detailsnews.php?nssl=64c06acc9a5858be426c2288782edd68&nttl=10052012110454 |archive-date=21 September 2013}}</ref> He was awarded CIP (Commercially Important Person) status in 2014 for his contributions in [[Bangladeshi RMG Sector|RMG sector of Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite news|title=147 get CIP cards|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/147-get-cip-cards-44230|work=The Daily Star|accessdate=Oct 4, 2014}}</ref>
==Early life and background== Ananta Jalil was born in [[Munshiganj District|Munshiganj]] and raised in Sukrabad, [[Dhaka]] along with his older brother by their father. His mother died when he was five years old.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Khan|first1=Jashim|title=দুধ বেচে জলিল এখন কোটিপতি|url=http://www.prothom-alu.co/2016/02/jalil-milk-vita.html|accessdate=6 February 2013|publisher=Prothom Alu|date=6 February 2013}}</ref>
In 1999 he started his profession as a Production general manager. Later he set up his small garment factory which further grown up to ''AJI Group'' year by year.<ref name="monsoonfilmsbd.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.monsoonfilmsbd.com/ananta/ |title=About Ananta |publisher=Monsoon Films |date= |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref> He was awarded CIP (Commercially Important Person) status in 2014 for his contributions in [[Bangladeshi RMG Sector|RMG]] sector.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bgmea.com.bd/home/pages/39_businessmen_get_CIP_status |title=39 businessmen get CIP status |publisher=Bangladesh Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Association |date= |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Rahman |first=Md Fazlur |date=8 January 2015 |title=The stellar rise of a garment maker |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/the-stellar-rise-of-a-garment-maker-58833 |newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref>
==Career==
Ananta made his debut as an actor and producer with the 2010 film ''[[Khoj: The Search]]''. The film headlined the debut of Ananta and [[Afiea Nusrat Barsha|Barsha]], [[Bobby (Bangladeshi actress)|Bobby]].<ref name="banglanews24.com"/> ''Khoj: The Search'' was followed by ''Hridoy Bhanga Dheu'' in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2017/01/09/ananta-jalil-barsha-become-maxx-colas-brand-ambassadors/|title=Ananta Jalil and Barsha become Maxx Cola's brand ambassadors {{!}} Dhaka Tribune|website=www.dhakatribune.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-06}}</ref>
In 2012, he appeared in two films, ''The Speed'' and ''[[Most Welcome]]''. Both the films were major commercial success and gave him breakthrough in [[Bangladeshi film industry|Bangladeshi cinema]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Esha |first=Rifat Islam |date=28 September 2012 |title=Most Welcome |url=http://newagebd.com/supliment.php?sid=120&id=884 |newspaper=[[New Age (Bangladesh)|New Age]] |location=Dhaka |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014011528/http://newagebd.com/supliment.php?sid=120&id=884 |archive-date=14 October 2013 |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref> In ''The Speed'', Ananta starred opposite to two foreign actresses, Malaysian actress Parveen and Russian actress Nana. The 2nd release ''Most Welcome'' was released on Eid.<ref>{{cite news|date=25 August 2012 |script-title=মোস্ট ওয়েলকাম টিকেট নিয়ে মারামারি |trans-title=Most Welcome hassle with tickets |url=http://www.dailyinqilab.com/august25/pdf/Bino+Corpo-25-08-12.pdf |newspaper=Daily Inqilab |language=bn |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120916110425/http://www.dailyinqilab.com/august25/pdf/Bino%2BCorpo-25-08-12.pdf |archive-date=16 September 2012 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>
In 2013 his only release was ''[[Nishwartha Bhalobasa]]''. The film marked the directorial debut of Ananta. Its story, dialogue, screenplay and lyric of a song was also written by him. It was premiered at 66th annual [[2013 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news |date=28 December 2013 |title='Niswartha Bhalobasha' premiered in city |url=http://news.priyo.com/2013/07/02/niswartha-bhalobasha-premiered-city-80144.html |newspaper=Priyo News |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref> The film was became a financial success.<ref>{{cite news |date= |title=10 of the Top Films of 2013 |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/entertainment/2013/dec/28/10-top-films-2013 |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune}}</ref> In 2014 ''[[Most Welcome 2]]'' was released'','' the squeal of his 2012 film ''Most Welcome''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ananta appears as police officer in Most Welcome 2 |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/entertainment/2013/nov/10/ananta-appears-police-officer-most-welcome-2 |newspaper=[[Dhaka Tribune]] |date=10 November 2013 |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref>
Ananta is the brand ambassador of [[Grameenphone]], a telecommunications service provider in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ananta Jalil is the new brand ambassador of GP |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/arts-amp-culture/2013/aug/24/ananta-jalil-new-brand-ambassador-gp |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |date= |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref>
==Personal life== Ananta is married to model-turned-actress [[Afiea Nusrat Barsha]] on 23 September 2011.<ref>{{cite news|date= |title=Ananta-Barsha: End of Innings??? |url=http://news.priyo.com/2013/03/27/ananta-barsha-end-innings-70254.html |newspaper=Priyo News |accessdate=20 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219055224/http://news.priyo.com/2013/03/27/ananta-barsha-end-innings-70254.html |archivedate=19 December 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> Barsha is the managing director of Monsoon Films.<ref name="ReferenceA">{{cite web |url=http://www.monsoonfilmsbd.com/barsha/ |title=Barsha |publisher=Monsoon Films |date= |accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref>
