'''Flotation cost''' is the total [[cost]] incurred by a [[company]] in offering its securities to the public. They arise from expenses such as [[underwriting]] fees, legal fees and registration fees. Firms are well advised to consider the magnitude of these fees as they also impact how much capital they can raise from an [[initial public offering]]. The more is the flotation cost the less viable is the source.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/277068142|title=A dictionary of business and management|date=2009|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199234899|edition=5th|location=Oxford [England]|oclc=277068142}}</ref>

