'''RenewableUK Cymru''' is the Wales branch of [[RenewableUK]], and is the trade body for all [[renewable energy]], and smart energy and storage technologies in Wales.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.renewableuk-cymru.com/our-expanded-remit/|title = RenewableUK Cymru website|date = |accessdate = 29 January 2015|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>
== History == RenewableUK Cymru's activities commenced in 2006 with the appointment of a full time Wales officer, Llywelyn Rhys.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.socme.org/may06downloads/bwea%20realpower05.pdf|title = Real Power Magazine|date = May 2006|accessdate = 30 January 2015|website = |publisher = British Wind Energy Association|last = |first = }}</ref> At that time RenewableUK was known as the British Wind Energy Association.
